Package space.sunqian.annotations

package space.sunqian.annotations
Annotations package, contains annotations supporting simple static analyses.
  • Annotation Interfaces
    Class
    Description
    CachedResult
    This annotation indicates that the return value of annotated method has already been cached using an appropriate caching strategy, and typically does not require additional caching.
    DefaultNonNull
    Declares all methods, fields, parameters, local variables, type parameters, and type uses under the scope of the annotated element must be non-null.
    DefaultNullable
    Declares all methods, fields, parameters, local variables, type parameters, and type uses under the scope of the annotated element is nullable.
    Immutable
    Declares the annotated element is immutable.
    NonExported
    This annotation indicates that the annotated method is non-exported.
    Nonnull
    Declares the annotated element must be non-null.
    Nullable
    Declares the annotated element is nullable.
    OutParam
    This annotation indicates that the parameter will be modified by the current method.
    RetainedParam
    This annotation indicates that the parameter will be used and held directly, any modification for this parameter may affect the behavior of the method or its return value.
    SimpleClass
    This annotation indicates that the annotated class is a simple class, it can be better optimized, such as optimizing it to a value class in the future version.
    ThreadSafe
    Declares the annotated element is thread-safe.
    ValueClass
    Declares the annotated class is a value class in the supported JVM.
